HEADWORD: Guib
<hw>Guib</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A West
African antelope (<spn>Tragelaphus scriptus</spn>), curiously marked
with white stripes and spots on a reddish fawn ground, and hence called
<altname>harnessed antelope</altname>; -- called also
<altname>guiba.</altname></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

